    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Catalan avant-garde movement in art and literature, founded in Barcelona in 1948 and active until the early 1950s. It was a counter-movement that wanted to break open the imposed art under the Franco regime. The style is based on Surrealism and Dadaism, but combined with Cubism and contemporary post-war trends, which opened Spanish art to foreign influences and made it the precursor of Spanish informal art and Abstract Expressionism. The movement published a magazine with the same name.</Note_Text>
